{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LJNC1GV46acKorkxnnSGmD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are satisfied. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `prometheus-config` ConfigMap only had a self-scrape job (`localhost:9090`) — no RabbitMQ targets.\n\n**Fix applied (two patches to the `prometheus-config` ConfigMap):**\n\n1. **Added `rabbitmq` scrape job** — targets all 3 pods via the existing headless service DNS (`rabbitmq-{0,1,2}.rabbitmq-headless:15692`, `/metrics` path).\n\n2. **Added a recording rule** — `rabbitmq_up := up{job=\"rabbitmq\"}`, since the native RabbitMQ Prometheus plugin (port 15692) doesn't expose a `rabbitmq_up` metric itself; Prometheus generates the `up` metric per scrape target, and the recording rule surfaces it under the expected name.\n\n3. **Hot-reloaded Prometheus** via `POST /-/reload` (no pod restart needed due to `--web.enable-lifecycle`).\n\n**Result:**\n- 3 RabbitMQ targets: all `up`\n- `rabbitmq_up` query: 3 samples, all value=1\n- All 3 RabbitMQ pods: `Running`, no restarts"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":707,"cache_read_input_tokens":39652,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":707},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc5ee1cb-df2f-4ed4-8a89-b5687c3dec66","uuid":"9a3a4cf9-d5f1-4a6d-ab8f-80d2cd1ea8ec","request_id":"req_011CcLGhcXZuBn7zmWAztqvX"}
